  "text": "The DPC model begins from the same starting point as the standard model: the neurophysiological finding that in many cases responses of cells within a cortical area can be predicted based on their tuning curves. Cell i's tuning curve, f i (x), describes its expected firing rate, typically defined as a spike count, as a function of the relevant dimension(s) x. These tuning curves are estimated by observing the cell's response on many trials using a set of stimuli that vary along x. A population code is defined to be a population of cells whose The distribution population coding framework shows how a distribution over can be encoded and then decoded from noisy population activities. From [CITATION_1] .",
